  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "AhO5vnVpcrkSsMeLDHig5V+LDZM=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:35.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "# Feed and Upload Counts\n\n## Single-user totals (for 1 drive + 2 docs)\n\n- 1 user manifest feed\n- 1 drive manifest feed (per drive)\n- 1 document manifest feed (per document)\n- Total: `1 + 1 + 2 = 4 feeds`\n\n## /bytes uploads\n\n- 1 per feed index update (the manifest JSON)\n- 1 per operation batch\n- Example: `4 manifest uploads + 2 op batch uploads = 6 /bytes refs`\n\n## Collaboration scaling (N users)\n\n- Each user writes to exactly 1 op feed per collaborative document\n- Each user reads N-1 op feeds per collaborative document\n- With GSOC/PSS push notifications, reads happen only on actual edits \u2014 bandwidth scales with edit frequency, not user count\n- Without push, every reader polls every peer feed \u2014 O(N) polling load\n\n## Design consequence\n\nFeed count grows linearly with documents, not sub-linearly \u2014 there is no \"one big feed\" compression. This is acceptable because feed creation is cheap; the expensive operation is `/bytes` uploads (stamp cost).\n",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:35.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:35.000Z"
    }
  },
